<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n25139i"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25139i">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25139i"> 139(i)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> that drowsyhead</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">It must not be imagined from this that bear-killing is an easy sport; on the contrary, it is extremely dangerous, for the fatigue and perils of <i>skid&aring;kning</i> the wild forests, with a very low temperature, for hours and hours is in itself a perilous pastime. Frost-bite is by no means uncommon, and, of course, in such cold, it is impossible to sit down and rest, lest <mark>that drowsy sleep</mark>, so dreaded in northern climates, should take hold of the weary man and gradually lull him into his last slumber. <small> Mrs Alec Tweedie, <a name="TTFC" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#TTFC"><cite title="source">Through Finland in Carts</cite></a> (1914) 190</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14089b" href="c14all.htm#c14089b">VI.C.14:089(b)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
